    "en": {
      "title": "Reset Sri Lanka reform conference by Advocata Institute",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 A forum on reforms needed to take Sri Lanka forward organized by Colombo based Advocata Institute is bringing together policy makers, international experts and the business community kicks of on August 05.",
        "The Let\u2019s Reset Sri Lanka forum will deal with vital reforms in areas such as taxation, State Owned Enterprise, social safety nets, trade policy and land policy.",
        "The two day forum is featuring eminent experts including Veerathai Santiprabhob, former Governor of the (Central) Bank of Thailand will be on the first day and Premachandra Athukorala from the Australian National University will be delivering his remarks on the second day of the conference."
      ],
